      "body" : "`gettransactions` simply does not give you inputs and outputs. It gives you \"ledger entries\" - effects that this transaction has on your wallet. If it contains an output that credits an address of yours, that will be represented as a receive, if it spends coins of yours they will be represented as a send (though with change subtracted).\r\n\r\nIf you're not interested in the wallet effects, but just in the actual inputs and outputs at the Bitcoin transaction level, yes, you'll have to use the raw data.\r\n\r\nAlso, `getrawtransaction` will not work unless you have a transaction index. Use @laanwj's suggested instead.",
      "created_at" : "2014-09-01T15:36:38Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/4807#issuecomment-54072727",
